  "text": "Trace how error E0505 'cannot move out of `x` because it is borrowed' is generated. The MIR borrow checker in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs detects a WriteKind::Move conflict via access_place(), which calls report_move_out_while_borrowed(). That method is defined in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/diagnostics/conflict_errors.rs, which delegates to cannot_move_when_borrowed() in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrowck_errors.rs. The borrowck_errors function creates a MoveBorrow diagnostic struct defined in compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/session_diagnostics.rs, annotated with #[diag(borrowck_cannot_move_when_borrowed, code = E0505)]. The error explanation is in compiler/rustc_error_codes/src/error_codes/E0505.md and registered in compiler/rustc_error_codes/src/lib.rs.",
